Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.16,0:00:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody asked about the severity of\Nmenopause. Um
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.28,0:00:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the the the mind is so powerful\Nthat what you hold in mind tends to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.64,0:00:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,manifest. Right? That's a pretty\Nwell-known generality. The whole course
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.72,0:00:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of miracles is based upon transcending\Nthat illusion that you are at the effect
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.35,0:00:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of anything out there.\NSo if a person is having severe symptoms
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.36,0:00:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,of anything menopause being one of them,\Nthe prevailing belief systems about
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.87,0:00:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,menopausal systems are sufficiently\Nstrong as to guarantee you you're
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.87,0:00:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,developing menopausal symptoms just out\Nof the fact that you automatically will
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.80,0:00:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,pick up that belief system from our\Nculture. There's no way to avoid it. You
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.71,0:01:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,turn on TV and there's, you know,\Nsomebody somebody pitching something for
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.39,0:01:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,menopause. So even if you don't believe\Nin menopause, you sure will if you hang
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.47,0:01:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,out in our society. And uh so that\Nprevailing thought form then you you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.36,0:01:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,give belief to it. The um truth as\Nreveal I I think the course of miracles
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.47,0:01:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is very excellent in that. Once you get\Nbelow beyond lesson 76, you realize that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.24,0:01:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you are not at the effect of anything\Nout there. Nothing out there has any
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.24,0:01:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,power over you. Unless you believe in\Nmenopause, you cannot get menopausal
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.52,0:01:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,symptoms.\NYou say, "Well, I don't believe in
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.20,0:01:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that." Yes, you do. Uh unconsciously,\Nyou're holding that or some aspect
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.20,0:01:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,within yourself is holding that as a\Ntruth. Because of that, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.28,0:01:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,manifesting. And I always tell people\Nwho have illnesses of one kind or
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.07,0:01:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,another, do the course of miracles and\Nhope for the best
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.32,0:01:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,because you don't know what your karma\Nis. But if you advance to a high degree,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.84,0:02:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you can transcend that karma and you\Nwon't even be subject to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.52,0:02:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,question.\N>> You see, because yeah, you because you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.68,0:02:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,see karma is a whole area for\Ninvestigation. In kinesiology, one of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.28,0:02:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the neatest things about it is you can\Nask questions about whether you got it
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.36,0:02:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in this lifetime or or did it come from\Nelsewhere? You know, um, everybody's
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.72,0:02:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,mean to me. Well, why do you suppose\Neverybody's mean to you? Well, because
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.36,0:02:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,if you were once mean to lots of people,\Nthey they've just been hanging on the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.87,0:02:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,other side waiting for you. And now\Nthey're getting even. So all all you can
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.59,0:02:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,do is u try to correct that karmic\Npropensity. Those are only propensities.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.64,0:02:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Karma is only propensities. Sometimes\Nit's so exact in its manifestation
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.08,0:02:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that you wonder uh it seems like more\Nthan a propensity.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.92,0:02:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,In the middle of that surgery I had on\Nthe groin. They did a hernia operation
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.44,0:02:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,with no anesthesia.\NI knew I knew and in fact I saw the guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.23,0:03:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I know exactly what I did. I saw the\Nerror was and I saw this was the undoing
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.16,0:03:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of it in my strict superego conscience.\NOnly by experiencing what he experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.76,0:03:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,could I\Nwrite the karmic wrong that I had done
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.95,0:03:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,out of what I took against myself is\Nspiritual cowardice. I didn't have the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.59,0:03:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,courage to finish the job\N>> there. I'm going to ask that question.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.56,0:03:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Does there was is there a physiological\Nresponse when an angel comes into your
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.48,0:03:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,aura? Yeah. Right. U in the in the early\Nearly stages and I'm going to get to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.76,0:03:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,your next question. In the earlier\Nstages the the experience I had was
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.08,0:03:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,uh a tingling like a tingling. No, it\Nwas like a flow of energy going up the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.20,0:03:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,spine going up your whole back. It was\Nexquisite. It was a sweet uh like a low
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.64,0:03:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,low energy orgasm almost. It was\Nexquisite and it just was continuous and
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.43,0:04:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it went up the back and it seemed to go\Nup the spine into the brain
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.64,0:04:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the brain it created a sweet\Nincredible sensation. And if you focused
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.64,0:04:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,over on this side, the sensation would\Nfocus to this side of the brain and this
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.15,0:04:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,side of the brain. And then it came down\Nand the experience was that when you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.75,0:04:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,went by something that needed some kind\Nof spiritual help, probably a group of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.36,0:04:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,people praying or something, this energy\Nwould was still exquisite. It would go
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.08,0:04:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,out the heart and go to that\Nuh automobile accident or people about
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.52,0:04:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to have a fight or couple uh arguing in\Na subway train or something and it would
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.40,0:04:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,go there and then sort of accomplish its\Npurpose and the people the argument
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.68,0:04:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,would stop and all of a sudden the\Nenergy would stop, you know. So that was
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.60,0:04:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that kind of energy.\NUh that kind of energy disappeared
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.00,0:04:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.68,0:04:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,so long as consciousness remained\Nstationary
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.60,0:05:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,uh there was no problem. But I think you\Ncan get tingling and uh all kinds of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.96,0:05:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,sensations and as I told you it got\Nfurther any kind of error within the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.63,0:05:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,aura was exquisitly painful. What were\Nyou going to ask? Um, what is your
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.84,0:05:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,experience with people who go into past\Nlives uh and might pick up an illness?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.52,0:05:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I've heard of people who have\Nbeen told they had cancer in a past life
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.75,0:05:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it became apparent in this\Nlifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.28,0:05:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes. So the question has to do with\Nkarmic propensities.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.28,0:05:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,One one value of kinesiologic research\Nis you can ask
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.72,0:05:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,um do I have permission to ask about\Nthis? Yes. Is this a propensity uh
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.96,0:05:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,coming through from other lifetimes?\NYes. Uh what was the you can then decide
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.16,0:05:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you know find out what was the decision\Nyou made. Don't forget they all have to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.88,0:05:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,do with intention. Something could be uh\Nyou could run over somebody with a
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.60,0:06:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,motorcycle but the intention was not\Nmurder. So
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.91,0:06:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,even the law recognizes the difference\Nbut it could be you know karma is a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.28,0:06:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,whole very difficult subject. It's not\Npopular in the west. It's karma is
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.44,0:06:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,confused with reincarnation. The two\Nthings are not the same thing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.84,0:06:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Karma is one thing, incarnation is\Nanother. Uh karma does not determine uh
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.24,0:06:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,they're two different subjects actually.\NJesus Christ did not to our knowingness
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.28,0:06:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,say much about it. He didn't say\Nanything about reincarnation, but he
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.84,0:06:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,sure did say plenty about karma.\NAll religions teach karma. All religions
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.88,0:06:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,teach that what you do in this lifetime\Nis going to have heavy duty consequences
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.80,0:06:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in your life next lifetime whether it's\Nphysical or not. There's absolute
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.68,0:06:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,agreement between all religions. Uh\Nkarma is why you avoid sin because you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.36,0:07:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,don't want to descend into the lower\Nastral.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.24,0:07:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Um karmic propensities. Um I I think\Nwith kinesiologic research you can find
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.16,0:07:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,out what you can about that. It it's\Nfunny. Most people have an intuitive
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.75,0:07:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,knowingness of if past lives were\Nsignificance. It's almost as if they
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.24,0:07:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,know it.\NIf somebody suggests you, you know, you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.47,0:07:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you you look just like, you know, you\Nact just like a pirate sometimes or look
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.96,0:07:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,like a pirate and you all sort of a and\Nyou're attracted to these motorcycle
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.12,0:07:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,guys who look like pirates. You know, I\Nrecognize these guys from uh they were
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.68,0:07:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the same guys that were on the ship. You\Nknow what I mean? I used to hire them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.24,0:07:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't raid other vessels with nimi\Npimpies. I'll tell you, you had to be
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.75,0:07:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you got to kill all the guys on the\Nother ship and steal their gold. I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.88,0:07:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't exactly be\Na pussyfoot. You know, they are pretty
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.91,0:07:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,rough guys. So I see him back, you know,\Nsame bandanna, same clothes, same
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.08,0:08:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,tattoos, same ring in the ear. Nothing's\Nchanged. They just changed them with,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.47,0:08:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, a ship for a motorcycle.\NHang out in gangs. It's the same damn
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.84,0:08:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,crew. Same people, right?\N>> What about grace, though? The power of
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.12,0:08:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,grace.\N>> Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.44,0:08:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Grace is.\Nalmost like the letting go of the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.03,0:08:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,sovereignty allows that which is\Nsovereign to intercede.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.31,0:08:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We call that intervention via the Holy\NSpirit generally, right? Yeah. That
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.68,0:08:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,through contrition, through uh\Nundoingness, through surrender and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.39,0:08:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,willingness\Nthat um
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.71,0:08:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,we create the space for the miraculous\Nwhich occurs as
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.64,0:08:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,termed as grace. Huh.\NEnlightenment itself is
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.56,0:09:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,by\NGod's grace
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.04,0:09:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,because all you can do is remove the\Nimpediments. You can only remove the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.44,0:09:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,impediments to higher consciousness. You\Ncannot cause higher consciousness to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.00,0:09:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,happen.\NYou can remove the impediments to love
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.08,0:09:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and then love takes over.\Nuh love having a higher energy tends to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.72,0:09:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,transform the event itself.\NSo we can remove the impediments but the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.95,0:09:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,final step is by God alone. You know God\Nonly
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.60,0:09:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that we call grace.\NGrace means that to our degree of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.88,0:09:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,knowingness, we could not possibly\Njustify it within any kind of reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.20,0:09:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The reprieve at the last instant even\Nthough you know you committed the crime
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.80,0:10:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet suddenly the reprieve come\Nthrough.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.36,0:10:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people say it's the earned karma,\Ngood karma from other lifetimes. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.32,0:10:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> What? What is the function of wanting\Nsomething better in life? If we if we
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.88,0:10:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,feel there's something which somehow\Ngives us the notion or the sense that
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.83,0:10:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that would be better and it's not\Nnecessarily a high spiritual thing but
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.95,0:10:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,just something we seem to naturally want\Nand then the sort of strength that
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.80,0:10:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,wanting focus on it often brings with it\NI find also a sense of a higher
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.51,0:10:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,vibration even though it's something not\Nnecessarily spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.76,0:10:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that following this higher\Nvibration, this goal, something which
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.56,0:10:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,pushes us along?\N>> It isn't necessarily following a higher
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.44,0:11:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,vibration. Intention is very powerful if\Nyou remove all the blocks to intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.56,0:11:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's it's possible to manifest things\Nthat would not otherwise be manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.68,0:11:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a one of the basic teachings of\NEST. You remember EST? very hard
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.20,0:11:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,seminars training. EST was very big as a\Nweekend workshop uh training back in the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.92,0:11:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,70s I think it was.\NUh EST would never allow you to have an
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.51,0:11:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,excuse to be late if the class started\Nat 8:00 and you showed up at 8:02.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.20,0:11:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You had to stop stand there until you\Nadmitted that you that you chose to be
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.64,0:11:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,late. So the person say, "Well, there\Nwas traffic and there was this and
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.51,0:11:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that." all these excuses\Nuh until you finally accepted that your
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.20,0:11:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,reason you're late is because you chose\Nto be late. They wouldn't let you in the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.20,0:11:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,door.\NWhy? Because you rated something higher
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.88,0:11:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,than being on time. So you actually\Nchose
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.56,0:12:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and you'd rather sleep late than get\Nleave early enough to make sure that no
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.32,0:12:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,delay would get in your way.\NResponsibility. So intention if you
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.88,0:12:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,remove all the blocks the ifs and ends\Nand buts in the if you remove all the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.07,0:12:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,excuses intention can be very very\Npowerful. It it's not that it's a
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.83,0:12:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,different energy or vibration doesn't\Nshow necessarily a move up the scale of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.48,0:12:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness but is much more likely to\Nto accomplish this objective.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.04,0:12:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what prevails when I catch\Nchickens.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.92,0:12:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing stands between me and catching\Nthe chicken. It's like a clear channel
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.76,0:12:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,opens between me and the chicken and\Nthis energy shoots through the through
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.63,0:12:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that opening. That's why I would never\Nengage in karate again or any of those
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.60,0:12:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,things because once you've got that\Nspace, you would just kill the other
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.68,0:12:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,person in an instant. There's no way\Nthey can stop it because
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.68,0:12:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,all considerations are removed.\NTherefore, the power shoots through you
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.36,0:13:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's the power itself that\Naccomplishes it. And death in one blow
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.27,0:13:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,would be a snap. Yeah. So intention then\Nis what accomplishes the seeming
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.07,0:13:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,impossible. Dedication. That intention,\Nthat dedication is what I was talking
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.80,0:13:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,about. When you walk to the razor's\Nedge, when you let every thought go as
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.12,0:13:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it begins to come up, the willingness to\Nsurrender it, surrender it, surrender
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.32,0:13:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it. Those of you that are in 12step\Nprograms, it'd be like you take the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.32,0:13:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,third step on every single impulse,\Nthought, feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.63,0:13:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,uh as it arises. The willingness to\Nsurrender everything to God. Um, and
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.48,0:13:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that's coming out of the heart.\NSomebody's been diagnosed as having an
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.24,0:13:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,illness. Uh well\Nin this case it has to do with attention
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.76,0:14:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,deficit disorder. I'll give you a\Npractical clinician's diagnosis of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.48,0:14:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,definition of how to diagnose ADD and\NADHD. I've had 50 years clinical
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.60,0:14:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,experience and right now I probably got\Nthree or 4 hundred patients with these
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.44,0:14:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,disorders.\NUh, as a pragmatist, ADD or ADHD is
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.07,0:14:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever it gets better with rolin.\NPeople have all kinds of fancy. They
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.72,0:14:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,want to do psychological testing. It's\Nusually a ch, you know, attempt to milk
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.24,0:14:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the parents. There's therapist for ADHD.\NGood luck. It's a neurologic condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.16,0:14:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's genetic. It's due to the fact that\Nin the pre-entral gyus, we have
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.92,0:14:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,suppressor strips. When you cut a\Nchicken's head off, it goes crazy,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.88,0:14:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,right?\NSo, the motor neurons automatically
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.88,0:14:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,respond via the spinal reflex, except\Nthat there's descending tracks that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.60,0:14:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,suppress it. These are coming from\Nsuppressor strips in the free pre-entral
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.32,0:15:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,gyus in the brain, the preoter gyrus.\NThe suppressor strips, if it wasn't for
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.39,0:15:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the suppressor strips, your your bodies\Nwould all be going in every which way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.24,0:15:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,See, because you're just dealing with a\Nspinal reflex. A spinal reflex. If I
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.39,0:15:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,touch this, this is going to jerk. It's\Nonly because of the suppressor strip
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.80,0:15:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that this doesn't jerk. Every time I\Ntouch it, every little breeze that goes
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.00,0:15:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,by would cause a spasm and a response.\NSo, the ADHD person is responding
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.36,0:15:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,constantly to stimuli that our\Nsuppressor strips hold down. See,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.39,0:15:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,they're always restless. They're always\Njumping around. They can't keep their
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.12,0:15:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,mind at one thing because of their\Ndistractability.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.12,0:15:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,uh what rin or some medication like that\Ndoes is stimulate the prefrontal
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.63,0:15:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,pre-entral gyus. So it activates the\Nsuppressor strip. So what would be a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.80,0:15:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,stimulant to a normal person is a\Nseditive to them and uh it's also used
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.44,0:16:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,uh in old folks home. A lot of old folks\Nblack coffee puts them to sleep because
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.60,0:16:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the suppressor the sleep sleep center of\Nthe brain is underactive. So you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.88,0:16:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,stimulate the sleep center and wake them\Nto go to sleep. So anybody who has ADHD
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.19,0:16:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,uh you use what is a trial dose of rolin\Nif they get instantly they get better
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.39,0:16:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,within an hour they'll tell you right\Naway I can sit still I can focus. I can
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.75,0:16:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,think I can behave. I can I can mind\Nwhen you say don't slam the door. or I
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.32,0:16:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,can remember to not slam the door that\Ndiagnoses it. U whether there's better
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.75,0:16:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,treatments or conditions, I don't know.\NUh the kinesiologic test, you know, is a
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.95,0:16:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is a tentative test. I would test it and\Nsay whether or not this person has it or
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.60,0:16:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't have it. If they have all the\Nsymptoms, though, I would certainly do a
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.07,0:16:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,trial of it. Why? Because an untreated\Ncase of ADHD then compounds itself. The
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.68,0:16:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,child can't behave. So, they begin to\Nget a self-concept that they're bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.04,0:16:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Other people don't like them. They feel\Nthe school's against them. They lose
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.56,0:17:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,their interest in learning. They drop\Nout, hang out in the street and do drugs
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.07,0:17:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and start robbing many stores. So\Nuntreated ADHD is worse than
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.52,0:17:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,misdiagnosing it. The worst thing that\Ncan happen is if you don't have ADHD and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.03,0:17:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,you take rin, you're going to be nervous\Nfor an hour or two like you drink too
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.83,0:17:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,many coffees. It's better to diagnose it\Nand treat it. And then if there's
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.48,0:17:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,behavioral means of overcoming it, God\Nbless them. I've never seen it happen,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.28,0:17:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but it could.\NWell, everything's possible to God,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.79,0:17:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,right?\NI've never seen anything about it. I
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.48,0:17:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,think they just It's a more of a\Npolitical position than a clinical
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.12,0:17:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,reality.\NThere's nothing wrong with having ADHD.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.79,0:17:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, except that if it's untreated,\Nyou get all kinds of negative feedback
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.72,0:17:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,from society, and that has the worst\Neffect.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.48,0:17:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Um,\Nand I don't know what this says.
